Based on the errors you provided, it seems that the `conn` and `stmt` variables are null when you are trying to invoke methods on them. We need to make sure these variables are properly initialized before invoking any methods on them.

Here is the updated and fixed version of the `testHealthWithNullConnection` and additional `testHealthWithNullStatement` test cases:

```java
import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;

import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import org.mockito.Mockito;
import java.sql.Connection;
import java.sql.SQLException;
import java.sql.Statement;


public class DatabaseHealthCheckTest {

    private DatabaseHealthCheck dbHealthCheck;
    private Connection conn;
    private Statement stmt;

    @BeforeEach
    public void setup() {
        dbHealthCheck = new DatabaseHealthCheck();
        conn = Mockito.mock(Connection.class);
        stmt = Mockito.mock(Statement.class);
    }

    @Test
    public void testHealthWithNullConnection() throws SQLException {
        // Set up mock behavior
        Mockito.when(conn.createStatement()).thenReturn(stmt);
        Mockito.when(stmt.execute("SELECT 1")).thenReturn(true);

        dbHealthCheck.setConnection(conn);
        assertTrue(dbHealthCheck.checkDatabaseHealth());
    }

    @Test
    public void testHealthWithNullStatement() throws SQLException {
        Mockito.when(conn.createStatement()).thenReturn(null);

        dbHealthCheck.setConnection(conn);
        assertFalse(dbHealthCheck.checkDatabaseHealth());
    }
}
```

In this updated version, we are mocking the `Connection` and `Statement` objects using Mockito to prevent them from being null. We also set up the mock behavior for the `Statement.execute` method to return true when the SQL query is "SELECT 1". Additionally, we added an extra test case (`testHealthWithNullStatement`) to handle the scenario where the `Statement` object is null.

Please make sure you have the necessary dependencies (such as Mockito) added to your project to successfully run these test cases. Let me know if you need further assistance.